<title>UK: RESEARCH ALERT-GUM raised to buy -Socgen.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT-GUM raised to buy -Socgen.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-08-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>Societe Generale said it had raised it recommendation on Russian department store GUM to a buy from a hold.</p>
<p>&quot;The current share price does not fully reflect the company's financial stability and its ability to achieve high and sustainable profits in both operating and ROE (return on equity) terms,&quot; it said in a note.</p>
<p>At the same time SocGen downgraded TSUM  TZUM.RTS from a weak buy to a hold following poor half-year results and difficulties in its renovation programme which suggested a turnaround would only occur in 1998 rather than 1997.</p>
<p>-- Ben Hirschler, London newsroom +44 171 542 6414</p>
